  "text": "During our epidemiological survey of Shigella, we collected 873 fecal samples from calves with diarrhea and obtained 54 S. flexneri isolates from five provinces in northwest China from 2014 to 2016. Isolate information is shown in detail in Table 2 . Among the 54 S. flexneri isolates, there were six serotypes: five (9.26%) isolates were 1a, twenty-six (48.15%) isolates were 2a, four (7.41%) isolates were 2b, six (11.11%) isolates were 4a, [CITATION_1] eight (14.81%) isolates were 6, and five (9.26%) isolates were Xv (Fig. 1 ). Our surveillance of the Gansu isolates identified all of the serotypes, except 4a. All 4a serotypes were isolated from Shanxi, while all Xv and 1a serotypes were from Gansu. Additionally, serotype 2a was widely isolated from each province, with the exception of Xinjiang, and serotype 6 was found only in yaks. Interestingly, Shigella was primarily isolated in the first quarter and fourth quarter, accounting for 54% (29/54) and 30% (16/54), respectively ( Fig. 2 ).",
